<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Congress To Guide China's Foreign Affairs (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The exposition of the
international situation and China's foreign policy in the report
by Jiang Zemin at the on-going Party Congress is of great
significance for guiding China's cross-century foreign affairs,
said Chinese diplomats here today.
</P>
<P>
The diplomats, who are delegates attending the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China, said Jiang's report has
carried forward and developed Deng Xiaoping's thinking on
diplomatic affairs, stressing the most outstanding characteristics
of the current international situation.
</P>
<P>
"The report has evaluated the achievements China has scored in
foreign relations over the recent five years and explained the
current international situation in a down-to-earth manner," said
Liu Huaqiu, director of the Foreign Affairs Office of the State
Council and vice-minister of foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
"The report has also worked out a principle for China's
diplomatic work in a down-to-earth manner," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tang Jiaxuan, vice-minister of foreign affairs, said Jiang
Zemin made a penetrating analysis of the current international
situation with a focus on the two themes in the present era --
peace and development.
</P>
<P>
He said the most important part in Deng Xiaoping's thinking on
diplomatic affairs is the formulation of correct principles and
policy after timely, proper analysis and judgement of the
international situation.
</P>
<P>
Shen Guofang, spokesman for the Ministry of Foreign Affairs,
noted the excellent and important point Jiang Zemin has made in
his report is to respect the diversity of the world and to work to
bring about a just and rational new international political and
economic order.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Congress To Guide China's Foreign Affairs (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In Tang Jiaxuan's view, it is an important point of Deng
Xiaoping's thinking on foreign affairs that foreign affairs should
not be handled on the basis of differences in social system and
ideology between countries. This point has also found expression
in Jiang Zemin's report to the Party Congress, which said: "We
should further improve and develop our relations with developed
countries on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence."
</P>
<P>
The most fundamental reason why China's diplomatic efforts in
the past five years could overcome difficulties to create a new
situation is that the Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at
the core has correctly implemented the thinking and theory of Deng
Xiaoping on diplomatic work and combine them with the country's
actual conditions, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We owe every major success we have won and every strategic
step we have taken to Deng Xiaoping's thinking on diplomatic
work," he added.
</P>
<P>
The essence and soul of the part contained in Jiang's report on
China's foreign affairs is the sentence: "It is necessary to adhere
to the ideas of Deng Xiaoping about diplomatic work and firmly
pursue an independent foreign policy of peace," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
Shen Guofang said: "Deng Xiaoping's ideas about diplomatic work
will continue to be the guiding ideology of our foreign affairs in
future."
</P>
<P>
Of course, the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the
core firmly implemented Deng Xiaoping Theory in the past five
years, succeeding in boosting China's economic development and
enhancing the comprehensive strength of the country.
</P>
<P>
Looking into the future of China's diplomatic work at the turn
of the century, Chinese diplomats held that challenges co-exist
with opportunities.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0003 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Congress To Guide China's Foreign Affairs (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A very important point Jiang has made in his report, Shen said,
is his exposition of the international situation. "For a fairly
long period of time to come, it will be possible to avert a new
world war and secure a favorable, peaceful international
environment," the foreign ministry spokesman quoted Jiang Zemin as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Jiang also pointed out that the present-day world is
still insecure. It is also a brilliant and dialectical exposition,
said Shen.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yongxiang, China's ambassador to the People's
Democratic Republic of Korea, said,"The remarks on foreign
affairs by Jiang Zemin have embodied China's highest national
interest, and we all Chinese diplomats must resolutely implement
them."
</P>
<P>
"It is an important guiding principle for our embassy work to
adhere to Deng Xiaoping's thinking on foreign affairs, opposing
hegemony, safeguarding world peace and developing good-neighborly
relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
The diplomats said that China's has scored outstanding
achievements in foreign affairs, which helped bring about an
excellent international relations.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqiu owed these achievements to the full implementation of
Deng Xiaoping's thinking on foreign affairs by the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
According to Shen Guofang, China has further improved relations
with its neighboring countries since the beginning of the 1990s in
accordance with the strategic principle set by Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
"Besides, we have withstood the pressure of 'sanctions' by a
few Western countries. So far, many countries, including some
Western countries, are willing to establish a new type of normal
and healthy cooperative relations with China geared to the 21st
century," said Shen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0004 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Congress To Guide China's Foreign Affairs (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To seize the opportunity and meet the challenge to create a
better international environment is to firmly implement the 10
basic principles set in Jiang Zemin's report on diplomatic work
and implement the independent foreign policy of peace.
</P>
<P>
As a permanent member state of the UN Security Council, Tang
said, China is to double its efforts for multi-lateral diplomatic
work. In the wake of a global trend toward multipolarity, China
should make new contributions to the development and peace in the
world.
</P>
<P>
The multi-lateral diplomatic work commands a wide range of
subject. It includes not only the United Nations and the
international organizations under it but also regional and
continent-to-continent political and economic organizations and
various kinds of seminars and talks in terms of economic
cooperation, safety and disarmament, he added.
</P>
<P>
"We should take an active part in these seminars and talks," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Shen Guofang said enthusiastic participation in the
multi-lateral diplomatic work is the requirement for establishing
a just and rational new international political and economic
order. It will further promote the global polarization, which
benefits the maintenance of world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqiu said the 10 basic requirements set in Jiang's report
is a historic conclusion based on experience. Therefore, it is of
historic significance. They are the reliable guarantee for
implementing the independent foreign policy of peace.
</P>
<P>
"By firmly implementing these requirements," Liu said, "we can
improve and develop our relations with surrounding countries,
strengthen solidarity and cooperation with other developing
countries, improve and expand relations with developed countries
on the basis of five principles of peaceful coexistence, make
progress in economic and technological cooperation and scientific
and cultural exchanges on the basis of equality and mutual
benefit, play a bigger role in the UN and other international
organizations, develop relations with political parties in other
countries and boost non-governmental diplomatic work," he said.
</P>
<P>
In this way, he said, China will further raise its
international status, exert more influence on international
affairs, and make fresh headway in its diplomatic work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
