<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Trails Russia in Race to Build AN-70 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, September 17 (Xinhua)-- Russia could soon be selling the
AN-70 military transport plane developed jointly with Ukraine to
foreign buyers while Ukrainian production lines for the aircraft
remain grounded, local newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Russian is getting ready to manufacture the plane while it's
still unclear when we will be able to start producing the AN-70
here in kiev," Antonov Design Bureau Director Petro Balabuyev was
quoted as saying at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
He said if money to start mass production at the Aviant plant
in Kiev was not available soon, Ukraine would lost AN-70 orders to
Russia.
</P>
<P>
Cash-strapped Ukraine and Russia agreed to share the high cost
of the AN-70's development and arranged production so that neither
country could take the lead in mass producing. Ukraine and Russia
are to assemble the planes independently but share the production
of components. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
