<HEADLINE> Six-storey Pharmacy collapsed in Yaounde </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A six-storey building named
"Pharmacie Monseigneur Vogt" located at Nsam on the outskirts of
Yaounde collapesd yesterday morning with two victims trapped
underneath, local paper Cameroon Tribune reported today.
</P>
<P>
After receiving the distress call from the area, a fire brigade
arrived at the scene in less than seven minutes to try to save the
trapped victims.
</P>
<P>
Enyegue Jean-marie, the proprietor of the pharmacy, watched
dejectedly as a caterpillar excavated the ruins of the collapsed
building. His son and his fiancee were still trapped underneath,.
and no one knows if they are alive or not, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Cameroonian Vice-Minister in charge of housing Hamadou
Moustapha came to the scene and deplored the hazardous methods of
construction of houses without following construction norms.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is not yet known, but the
vice-minister attributed the accident to poor quality building
materials used in the construction of the building. 
</P>
</TEXT>
