<HEADLINE> Iran Launches Most Extensive Military Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Iran today unfolded its most
extensive joint military exercises ever in Koushk-Nosrat and
around the Qom lake, about 150 kilometers south of capital Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that 200,000 troops
of the navy, ground and air forces took part in the first stage of
the week-long war games code-named Zolfaqar.
</P>
<P>
The joint military exercises are a very effective means of
displaying the capability and defense strength of the army in
dealing with possible threats, military experts said.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier-General Mohammad Mahmoudi said that 10 independent
divisions or brigades and artillery units took part in today's
maneuvers.
</P>
<P>
The participating troops backed by heavy artillery fire
advanced toward hypothetical enemy positions while parachutists on
board C-130 cargo planes landed behind the enemies, he said.
</P>
<P>
After capturing the enemy positions, they then launched
mopping-up operations with support of choppers, he added.
</P>
<P>
Mahmoudi said this stage of the exercises were aimed to prepare
the forces for the main attack.
</P>
<P>
Major General Ali Shahbazi, chief of the joint staff of the
Iranian army, said earlier that the exercises would be an
expert-level one comprising different drillings including defense
against chemical attacks and electronic warfare, to be overseen by
some 200 military experts.
</P>
<P>
According to him, Iranian-made planes and tanks would be tested
and live ammunition would be used throughout the operations.
</P>
</TEXT>
