<HEADLINE> CPC Central Committee Extends Thanks to Non-Communist Parties (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The letter said that all non-Communist parties and the
All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce have united and
cooperated with the CPC for over half a century.
</P>
<P>
They are long-tested and close friends of the CPC, the letter
said, and are major forces to rely on to develop the patriotic
united front, safeguard the stability and solidarity of the
country, and build socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The letter pointed out that China's reforms and modernization
drive have entered a new crucial period.
</P>
<P>
While facing a bright future, the letter added, the CPC will
further consolidate and develop the patriotic united front, and
the broadest alliance composing all socialist laborers and all
patriots who support socialism and the reunification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The letter said that the policy of "long-term coexistence and
mutual supervision, and treating each other honestly and sharing
weal and woe" will be unswervingly upheld, and the multi-party
cooperation system and the political consultative system under
the leadership of the CPC will be adhered to and improved.
</P>
<P>
The CPC will further develop a closely cooperative relationship
with each non-Communist Party and the All-China Federation of
Industry and Commerce, in which they will treat each other on an
equal footing and unite with each other in marching forward, the
letter said.
</P>
<P>
The letter said that the CPC ardently hopes that non-Communist
parties would actively participate in the political affairs and in
democratic supervision.
</P>
<P>
Finally, the letter called for all to hold high the great
banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, and work together to make greater
contributions to the revitalization and prosperity of the country
and the reunification of the motherland. 
</P>
