<HEADLINE> 15th National Party Congress Elects New Central Committee (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the basis of democratic recommendation and after serious
scrutiny and repeated deliberation, the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the 14th CPC Central Committeed held several
meetings to study the recommendation lists and the Political
Bureau held a plenary meeting to discuss and decide the
recommendation lists of the preliminary candidates of members and
alternate members of the 15th CPC Central Committee and of the
members of the new CCDI.
</P>
<P>
During the congress, the delegates earnestly discussed and
pondered over the recommendation lists of the preliminary
candidates submitted by the Political Bureau of the 14th CPC
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The delegates vied with one another for giving their opinions
and fully expressed their views in a democratic and warm
atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
The delegates showed their full approval of the work on
recommendation, examination and nomination of candidates.
</P>
<P>
The delegates thought that the most significant characteristics
the process of recommendation, examination and nomination were
adherence to the principle of democratic centralism.
</P>
<P>
They said that full play has been given to democracy, that the
work has been done meticulously and that every aspect has been
taken into account.
</P>
<P>
The personnel preparation of the 15th National Party Congress
has proved that the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the
core is a strong and united collective leadership, the delegates
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
