<HEADLINE> 15th National Party Congress Elects New Central Committee (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The delegates showed their approval and support for the plan of
personnel arrangement which they considered fine.
</P>
<P>
The plan showed that the candidates are highly qualified and
its age pattern is reasonable with a composition of members of
different age groups from the young to the elder.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the delegates noted, a group of people who are
in their prime of life and with both ability and political
integrity have been nominated as candidates, among whom there are
outstanding figures from various fields.
</P>
<P>
The delegates unanimously agreed that the new CPC Central
Committee is certainly able to hold high the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory in leading the whole Party and the people of all
nationalities to fulfill all strategic tasks set forth by the
current congress, and to push forward the great cause of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The delegates also offered opinions and suggestions about the
plan of personnel arrangement.
</P>
<P>
With a highly responsible attitude toward the Party and the
people, the delegates practiced their democratic rights and
elected the new CPC Central Committee and the new CCDI through
preliminary election in which there were more candidates than
scheduled seats and through formal election in which there was a
same number of candidates and seats.
</P>
