<HEADLINE> 15th National Party Congress Elects New Central Committee (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the new CPC Central Committee, there are a number of Party
veterans who have stood tests of revolutionary struggles, have
rich experience in leadership and are familiar with the Party's
fine traditions and good style of work.
</P>
<P>
There is also a number of middle-aged members who have been
tempered for two or three decades in the Party and who are loyal
to the Party undertakings.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, a group of young cadres with both ability and
political integrity have been added to the new Central Committee,
which shows that the Party leadership enjoys smooth replacement of
the elder ones by younger ones and good cooperation between them.
This also shows that there is no lack of successors in the Party,
the delegates said.
</P>
<P>
The new CPC Central Committee is composed mainly of leading
officials at above provincial (ministry) level, and also comprises
other leading officials and outstanding Party members from various
quarters of society.
</P>
<P>
The committee includes a total of 303 leading officials at or
above the deputy provincial governor (vice-minister, deputy
commander of greater military area) level, accounting for 88.1
percent of the total.
</P>
</TEXT>
