<HEADLINE> Tibetans Support Unity, Stability of Motherland (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Tibetans have displayed strong
support for the unity and stability of the motherland during the
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Numerous well-known Tibetans who have returned from abroad have
praised Jiang Zemin's work report presented at the opening of the
congress. They were especially pleased with Jiang's stress on
upholding the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory and modernizing
Tibet.
</P>
<P>
"Jiang's report summarized China's experiences over the past
century and outlined the country's long-term plan," according to
Gyibug Puncogcedain, a member of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC). "I'm
fully confident of future economic development in Tibet."
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan splittist clique headed by the Dalai Lama is intent
on hindering social stability and economic development in Tibet
and can in no way win support from the people, said
Puncogcedain. "We will closely unite around the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core and maintain a clear mind
in order to promote national unity and economic development."
</P>
<P>
According to an official from the Regional Nationality and
Religious Affairs Commission, "Tibet has achieved notable progress
in all fields since the introduction of the reform and opening
drive and we must treasure hard-earned stability."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
