<HEADLINE> France Wishes U.S. to Stay on in Bosnia After July 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 18 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine today expressed hope that the United States to maintain a
kind of presence in Bosnia after the NATO-led Stabilization Force
(SFOR) ends its mission in July 1998.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the United States decide to stay beyond the
announced date, even if this presence takes a different form,"
said Vedrine during a meeting with the press.
</P>
<P>
The United States is participating in the mission of SFOR,
deployed to guarantee the implementation of the Dayton peace
agreement signed in November 1995. But Washington has announced
that the U.S. troops will withdraw when the SFOR completes its
mission.
</P>
<P>
Most European countries participating in the peace mission in
Bosnia have indicated that they will withdraw their troops if the
Americans do. 
</P>
</TEXT>
