<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Give Factory Ownership to Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- As part of the Bangladesh
government's denationalization program, the ownership of five
factories would be given to the workers or respective units, Prime
Minister Sheikh Hasina was quoted by the press as saying today.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with leaders of the Bangladesh Workers Party today, the
prime minister said the workers would be the sole owners of these
mills and factories and they would enjoy profits as well as
losses, according to the official news agency BSS.
</P>
<P>
The mills and factories would not be allowed to be used for
other purposes such as housing projects, the prime minister
stressed.
</P>
<P>
She noted that the aim of the denationalization program is to
revitalize the existing industrial units and avoid the destruction
of more cropland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
