<HEADLINE> Hi-tech Invention Exhibition Draws Handy Citizens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 18 (Xinhua) -- New hi-tech daily-use
products attracted great attention at today's opening of the Tenth
National Invention Exhibition in this capital city of south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The 1,000-plus products on exhibit included a number of items
from the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong exhibits include a powerful telecommunications
chip which can be used with mobile phones. The product, which was
developed by a Hong Kong company, is one of the first of its kind
in the world.
</P>
<P>
Exhibition sponsors report that innovative ideas and products
display at the exhibition were selected from numerous entries from
throughout China, and that relevant authorities appraised all
products as having great commercial potential.
</P>
<P>
A Chinese dictionary which also serves as a manual for entering
Chinese characters on a computer keyboard attracted great
attention on opening day. The dictionary holds a Hong Kong patent.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the exhibition is to transform inventions into
productive forces, according to a representative of the China
Inventors Association.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will provide inventors with a venue for finding
buyers for their ideas.
</P>
<P>
The association is sponsoring the exhibition with assistance
from the city of Guangzhou. The city and provincial governments
invited the participation of numerous local enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The annual exhibition, held in a different provincial capital
each year, was first held in 1988 and has since become one of the
nation's largest science and technology fairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
