<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0045 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Trade Official Confident in Enterprise Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The theoretical breakthroughs
in the exposition of ownership made by the 15th National Congress
of the Communist Party of China will further promote the reform of
China's state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhongyu, minister in charge of the State Economic and
Trade Commission, said progress will be made in the reorganization
of state-owned enterprises, readjustment of economic structures
and enterprise merge and bankruptcy.
</P>
<P>
The state will place special emphasis on managing well 1,000
key large state-owned enterprises based on the experiment in 512
large enterprises while adopting a more flexible policy in other
state-owned enterprises, Wang said in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The major tasks in the reform of state-owned enterprises will
be structural readjustment, reducing the swelling structure which
is resulted from overlapping construction and intensifying the
work on enterprises'merger and bankruptcy, he said.
</P>
<P>
This year, China is to increase the amount of funds earmarked
for writing off bad debts caused by bankruptcy of state-owned
enterprises from this year's 30 billion yuan to 40 billion yuan in
1998, he said.
</P>
<P>
Though some state-owned enterprises are still in difficulty,
preliminary results have been achieved in the readjustment and
reform of the state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, Wang said, the amount of
profits gained by the state-owned enterprises increased by 115
percent compared with that in the same period of last year.
State-owned enterpriss in 20 provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities, or two thirds of the national total, have improved
their efficiency so far this year.
</P>
<P>
However, the reform will not prevent all enterprises from
bankruptcy. The joint stock system will play a bigger role in
enterprise reform, he added.
</P>
<P>
"We should neither rush headlong into mass action nor demand
mandatory practice in implementing the shareholding system and
joint stock partnership," he said.
</P>
<P>
China will speed up development of capital market. Direct
fund-raising is to be a major channel to increase capital for
state-owned enterprises. Meanwhile the flow of capital through
market will be a principal form in building enterprise groups,
Wang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
