<HEADLINE> Dongyang Donates to University in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Dongyang City in east China's
Zhejiang Province, one of the many Chinese provinces witnessing
rapid economic growth, recently donated 10 million yuan (1.2
million US dollars) to the Beijing University of Science and
Engineering.
</P>
<P>
Today's edition of Science and Technology Daily quoted Wang
Yue, president of the university, as saying that the donation will
enable the university to contribute more to the development of
Dongyang City.
</P>
<P>
A year ago, Dongyang City and the university signed a
cooperation agreement covering science, technology and education.
</P>
<P>
By using high technology developed by the university, Dongyang
is now able to produce a new phosphorus-free washing powder and
has upgraded titanium plating for metals.
</P>
<P>
The university also trained a number of personnel for the
city.  
</P>
