<HEADLINE> Major Bridge Across River Opened in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A major bridge across the
Ayeyawaddy River in Myanmar was inaugurated today, witnessed by
Chairman of the State Law and Order Restoration Council Than Shwe,
according to the state-run Radio Myanmar this evening.
</P>
<P>
The 1,254-meter Nawadei Bridge at Pyay City in Bago Division is
the second bridge across the river, which flows from north to
south for a distance of about 2,000 kilometers. There was only the
Innwa Bridge across the river in the past.
</P>
<P>
Four more new bridges are under construction.
</P>
<P>
The Ayeyawaddy River delta is known as the "Rice Bowl of
Myanmar" with a total area of some 33,657 square kilometers.
</P>
</TEXT>
