<HEADLINE> Lufthansa, Karstadt Seal Merger of Tourism Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Germany's national airline Lufthansa
and retail group Karstadt today announced plans to merge their tourism
operations to deal with heightening competition in the European
tourism market.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement approved by the two companies on Thursday, a
joint venture would be set up on November 1 this year which would
combine Lufthansa's charter airline Condor and Karstadt's travel group
NUR. Both companies would hold a 50 percent stake in the venture.
</P>
<P>
