<HEADLINE> Beijing Mobile Phone Users </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The number of mobile phone
subscribers in the Chinese capital city has soared by 200,000 to a
total of over 500,000 in the past seven months.
</P>
<P>
The city has witnessed annual 100 percent growth in mobile
phone subscriptions since 1987. Said figures indicate that the
Chinese capital has reached international levels in terms of
mobile and data communications.
</P>
<P>
The number of local mobile phone users rose from a mere 10,000
in 1992 to over 300,000 in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Some 370,000 subscribers use GSM mobile phones, with the
130,000 subscribers using analog units.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Telecom has installed 360-odd local GSM base stations
locally which function city-wide, including in the capital's
extensive subway system. The system also offers roaming services
for 31 provinces, municipalities, and autonomous regions, as well
13 countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
