Yeltsin said today that Russia would accept no financial aid from
the International Monetary Fund (IMF) starting from 1999, local
press reported.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin made the remarks during his one-day inspection of the
Orel region near Moscow.
</P>
<P>
He said Russia will carry on reforms by relying on itself from
1999 though it will continue receiving IMF aid in 1997 and 1998.
</P>
<P>
