<HEADLINE> Party's New Central Committee Has More Young People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) closed here this morning after
electing a new CPC Central Committee, of which 21 members and
alternate members are under 45 years old.
</P>
<P>
In the previous central committee, there were only 14 members
and alternate members of this age group.
</P>
<P>
The new central committee has a total of 193 members and 151
alternate members.
</P>
<P>
The congress also elected a new Central Commission for
Discipline Inspection (CCDI) with 115 members.
</P>
<P>
As compared with the previous Party Central Committee, a group
of young and middle-aged cadres has been added to the new
committee, whose members and alternate members have an average age
of 55.9.
</P>
<P>
Among them, those above 61 years of age number 68, or 19.8
percent of the total; those between 56 and 60 years old reach 118,
or 34.3 percent; those between 51 and 55 number 107, or 31.1
percent; those under 50 account for 51, or 14.8 percent. 
