<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Multiple Telephone Lines for Shanghai Households </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Telephone
Bureau has introduced a new service offering preferential prices
to two telephone lines per household.
</P>
<P>
Some 499 households in Shanghai have applied for the service,
and some 88 households are already enjoying the benefits of two
telephone lines.
</P>
<P>
The widespread use of computer networks and hot line telephone
services necessitated two line for various Shanghai families.
</P>
<P>
Most applications for two telephone lines are avid computer
users or businessmen, according to the Shanghai Telephone Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Some 2.5 million households in Shanghai had had telephones by
the end of June, accounting for 55 percent of the city's total.
</P>
<P>
Currently, telephone lines are installed in more than 800
households on a daily basis. 
</P>
