<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Population Grows by 3 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The estimated mid-1997
population of Hong Kong is 6,502,100, according to figures
released today by the Census and Statistics Department, the
Government Information Service (GIS) of Hong Kong reported today.
</P>
<P>
There was an increase of 191,100 persons as compared with the
mid-1996 population estimate, representing a growth rate of three
percent.
</P>
<P>
The balance of arrivals and departures showed a net inflow of
some 158,800 persons from mid-1996 to mid-1997, constituting 83
percent of the population growth.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, there were 62,900 births and 30,600
deaths in Hong Kong. The natural increase thus amounted to 32,300,
accounting for 17 percent of the population growth.  
</P>
