<HEADLINE> CHINA SATCOM '97 Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- CHINA SATCOM '97, a symposium
sponsored by the China Users Association of Satellite
Communications, Broadcasting and Television, opened in Beijing
today.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the association told Xinhua that the two-day
conference is aimed at helping Chinese users to acquaint
themselves with latest developments in satellite communications,
broadcasting and television sectors over recent years.
</P>
<P>
The fledgling communications technology, including satellite
communications, has developed rapidly globally and in China, and
it is playing a growing bigger role in information networks, the
sources say.
</P>
<P>
Participants will share their views on the newly-developed
satellite communicational systems, satellite television systems,
and related technology as well as China's laws and regulations in
the field.
</P>
<P>
A series of seminars, technical exchange, panel discussions and
new products' presentations will also be held. 
