<HEADLINE> Editorial Hails Successful Conclusion of 15th Party Congress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- People's Daily, the organ of
the Central committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
warmly hails the successful conclusion of the 15th National Party
Congress in an editorial to be published on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Calling it "an epoch-making Congress", the paper said that the
whole Party and the people of the whole country are rejoiced at
the event for it was convened at a crucial moment of the country's
reforms and opening-up and it has carried forward the cause and
forged ahead into the future; it has held high the great banner of
Deng Xiaoping Theory and has unswervingly adhered to the correct
line formulated since the Third Plenum of the 11th Party Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
It is also a meeting which has mobilized the whole Party and
people of the entire country to unite and strive for an all-round
advancement of the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The greatest contribution of the congress was to establish Deng
Xiaoping Theory as the guiding ideology of the Party, it said.
</P>
<P>
"As an important milestone, the congress will shine forever in
the history of our Party and the state," the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin's report to the congress on behalf of the 14th CPC
Central Committee has won the praise of all the delegates and the
warm support from the whole Party and the people of the country,
the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
Based on Deng Xiaoping Theory and the Party's basic line, the
report summed up the rich experience gained in the past two
decades since the reforms and opening-up, especially since the
convening of the 14th National Party Congress in 1992, and put
forward the basic program for the primary stage of socialism and
outlined the strategy for the great cross-century cause, it
continued.
</P>
<P>
It has proved that the third generation of China's central
leading collective with Jiang Zemin at the core is the reliable
successor to Deng Xiaoping Theory and the great cause pioneered by
Deng, the editorial stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
