<HEADLINE> Mercenary Hired Against Sierra Leone Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, September 18 (Xinhua)--Sierra Leone military sources
said today that a locally based international diamond mining
company run by two Israelis has hired a mercenary group to
overthrow the military government.
</P>
<P>
According to the high level sources, the Israelis have already
paid the South African Executive Outcomes (EO) a part payment or
one million U.S. Dollars of the six million Dollars which the
entire operation will cost.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian soldiers serving in the West African peacekeeping
Force in Liberia have also been accused as "part of the
operation," the source said.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Ministry of Mineral Resources confirmed the
allegation and said that three agents of the Company are now
being questioned by security officials.
</P>
<P>
"I cannot yet tell you whether those being questioned are
locals or foreigners. It is a much sensitive issue," he added.
</P>
<P>
According to one geologist, Israeli firms operating in Sierra
Leone control half of the rich diamond fields in the east of the
country especially in Zimmi and Tongo.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that last year, Sierra Leone produces about one
million carats which should have fetched a minimum of 200 million
Dollars in gross domestic output.
</P>
<P>
"Smuggling and other corrupt practices have made some 800
highly valued carats not to be accounted for," he added.
</P>
<P>
The EO was first hired by the military regime of Captain
Valentine Strasser in 1992 to fight against the then rebels of
the Revolutionary United Front (RUF) but the contract was
terminated by the ousted civilian government of Tejan Kabbah in
1996 in which the group was paid over four million Dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
