<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rebels Abduct 9 Civilians in W. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the Allied
Democratic Forces (ADF) abducted nine civilians in Kasese
district, western Uganda, local paper, The Crusader, reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said about 30 rebels looted the shops in suburb of
Kasese town center.
</P>
<P>
The well armed rebels did not shoot in the action, obviously
to avoid alerting soldiers or policemen usually patrolling the
area.
</P>
<P>
The rebels disappeared in the direction to Rwenzori mountains
where is believed to be the hideout of ADF.
</P>
<P>
The rebel action confirmed by Lt. Colonel Charles Angina, the
operation commander in the west.
</P>
<P>
But the commander refused to reveal any further details about
the activities of the rebels due to security reason. "I can't
ascertain exactly that it is your voice," he said, adding "rebels
are not people who only stay in the mountains and jungle, but
even stay in towns."
</P>
<P>
A security source in the district said the rebels raided the
area around 02:00 am, just moments after a police/army patrol
changed their direction.
</P>
<P>
By noon yesterday, three of the abducted succeeded in escaping
from the rebels, and still other two were rescued by local
policemen, the report said.
</P>
<P>
ADF is a rebel group acting in the west with some 350
soldiers, a recent official report said. It had some 1,500
fighters last November. ADF abducts civilians to fill their
ranks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
