<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spokesman on UN Decision on Taiwan Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Taiwan authorities'
attempt to create "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan" has once
again been proven unpopular and doomed to fail, a Chinese Foreign
Ministry spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman made the remark to reporters at a routine weekly
press conference when asked to comment on the fact that the
General Committee of the 52nd UN General Assembly again rejected
the motion of a small number of countries to put the issue of
Taiwan's representation in the United Nations on the agenda of the
General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
This gives an eloquent proof that any act in violation of the
objectives and principles of the UN charter, as well as relevant
UN resolutions, or any move interfering in another country's
internal affairs will be opposed by the international community,
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the No. 2758 UN resolution reached in 1971 has
already solved the issue of China's representation in the UN
fairly and completely.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan, as one region of China, is not at all qualified to join
the United Nations as an entity apart from China, the spokesman
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
