<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Water Conservancy Effort Paid Off in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Autonomous Region is
reaping the success of its water conservancy efforts over the past
five years.
</P>
<P>
A comprehensive hydrological network has been basically
completed which can supply water and electricity to the region and
enhance flood and drought control.
</P>
<P>
Since 1972, funding totaling 1.5 billion yuan from both the
central and local governments has gone toward over 300 water
conservancy projects, most of which have contributed significantly
to the regional agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The regional government has always given priority to those
projects in poor counties aiming to improve local living and
farming conditions.
</P>
<P>
A canal project in Rinbung County in Xigaze Prefecture
increased the crop yields by 150,000 kilograms the same year it
was completed and put into use.
</P>
<P>
Another in Tingri County has added more than 300,000 kilograms
of grain each year to farmers' granaries, putting an end to the
food shortage problem in the area.
</P>
<P>
The past five years saw the completion of 35 new hydropower
stations in Tibet which provide an additional 66 million
kilowatts/hours to the regional power supply, as well as clean
drinking water to some 48,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The newly-built dykes and dams with a total length of 188
kilometers have greatly enhanced Tibet's capacity to fight floods
and mud-rock flows. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Succeeds in Growing Vanilla </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Some 133-ha of vanilla plants
are doing well in Xishuangbanna area, southwest China's Yunnan
Province, with some already in full bloom.
</P>
<P>
This marks a success for the country to grow vanilla on a large
scale. In the 1970s, the province's scientists did experiments in
the area and made progress.
</P>
<P>
In 1985, the province spent a million yuan on a vanilla
research project for high-yielding techniques.
</P>
<P>
Vanilla is widely used in the making of cigarettes, wine, tea,
foodstuffs, beverages, cosmetics, and perfume. But only a few
countries produce vanilla due to climate limitations.
</P>
<P>
The province invested large amounts of funding into building
the Yunnan Vanilla Industrial Co., Ltd. in 1994. Now, the company
has a curing factory with an annual capacity of 300 tons. Last
year, it produced 1.5 tons of beans and five tons of vanilla bean
flavoring.
</P>
<P>
The company expects to yield 60 tons of beans by the end of the
century when all the 133 ha begin to bear fruit. It plans to
expand the growing acreage to some 667 ha and have an annual
output of 300 tons of beans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
