<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Asks Youngsters to Support Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Young people in the
prosperous city of Guangzhou, capital of Guangdong province, are
being asked to contribute their pocket money to an environmental
protection foundation.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou City Communist Youth League Committee suggested
that they set up savings accounts and donate the interest to the
fund, which was established recently.
</P>
<P>
Some 500,000 yuan (63,000 US dollars) were deposited on the day
the fund was launched, sources said. Guangzhou has 1.2 million
primary and high school students.
</P>
<P>
A lack of public awareness among the adult population is
usually blamed for the increased pollution in Chinese urban
areas. Many people believe that the youngsters who are more
familiar with modern technology will show greater interest in
environmental protection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
