<HEADLINE> Bodies of 5 Iranians Flown to Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Bodies of five Iranians
cadets, who were killed by terrorists Wednesday in Pakistan, were
flown to the Iranian capital of Tehran this morning on a special
aircraft of the Pakistan Air Force.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Religious and Minorities Affairs Raja Zafar-ul-Haq
and other senior officials who accompanied the bodies will convey
condolences on behalf of the government and people of Pakistan to
the Iranian government.
</P>
<P>
Zafar-ul-Haq said the incident jolted the whole nation.
</P>
<P>
"It is a shameful act that people from a Muslim brother country
were killed by unidentified terrorists," Zafar-ul-Haq said.
"Pakistan is unfortunately in the grip of terrorism, which is a
matter of deep concern for the government."
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif has already ordered a high-level
inquiry to probe the incident, arrest the culprits and give them
exemplary punishment, Zafar added.
</P>
<P>
The Iranians were shot dead on Wednesday by unidentified gunmen
in Rawalpindi, a sister city of Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
Before departure, a funeral was offered for the five dead at a
military camp here. Foreign Minister Gohar Ayub Khan, Minister of
State for Foreign Affairs Siddique Kanju, the three Services
chiefs, government officials and diplomats of the Iranian embassy
here attended the prayers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
