<HEADLINE> Party Congress As Seen in Ordinary People's Eyes (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Workers at the New Shipyard
in northeast China's port city of Dalian in northeast China's
Liaoning Province have been doing their jobs with zeal since the
15th CPC National Congress opened last Friday. More than 1,000 of
them spent last weekend working.
</P>
<P>
"Our shipyard built ships totaling 500,000 DWT in 1996, more
than any other shipyard in the country," said Yuan Tongsheng, a
worker at the shipyard. "We could never have attained this goal
without the guidance of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics and the reform and
opening-up policy."
</P>
<P>
"We have set 600,000 DWT as this year's goal," Yuan said.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping proposed that Chinese-built ships should become
more prominent on the international market when China's
shipbuilding industry turned sluggish, recalled Wang Lianyou,
secretary of the Shipyard Party Committee. "It is in accordance
with his instruction that our shipyard signed the first group of
export contracts in 1980."
</P>
<P>
He said that the design and building capacity of his shipyard
has met the advanced world standards following ten years of work.
</P>
<P>
The factory has produced nearly two million DWT of ships, 98
percent of which are for export. It now has ship orders of 1.69
million DWT, which are worth 740 million US dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We will double our efforts to meet the requirement defined by
President Jiang Zemin in his report on efficiently operating the
state-owned enterprises at the 15th CPC National Congress," said
Wang Xin, an official with the shipyard.
</P>
</TEXT>
