<HEADLINE> Party Congress As Seen in Ordinary People's Eyes (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sun Xishan, chairman of the Association of Taiwan-Funded
Companies in Sanya City, south China's Hainan Province, said that
he chosed to stay in Haikou and celebrate the success of the
congress with the local people rather than return to his hometown
to enjoy Moon Festival activities.
</P>
<P>
He said that during this traditional Chinese festival for
family reunions, President Jiang Zemin's speech on the
peaceful reunification of the motherland appears to be creative,
sincere and promising.
</P>
<P>
"The topic of reunification is just like the bright moon, which
attracts the attention of people on both sides of the Taiwan
Straits," Sun said.
</P>
<P>
"I am moved by Jiang's statement that he places his hope on
the patriotic Taiwan compatriots," he said. "As a Taiwan
businessman, I am duty-bound to contribute to the reunification of
the motherland."
</P>
<P>
Many Taiwan compatriots are waiting to see how the "one
country, two systems" principle will be implemented in Hong Kong
and then in Macao, he said, adding that the great principle put
forward by Deng Xiaoping may lead to a eventual solution to the
Taiwan question.
</P>
<P>
Sun has invested more than 150 million yuan (18 million US
dollars) in the Chinese interior area and has decided to invest
more in Shenzhen, south China's Guangdong Province, after the
congress.
</P>
</TEXT>
