<HEADLINE> Palestinians Clash With Israeli Soldiers in Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Israeli security forces
detained five Palestinians overnight in a stone-throwing clash in
the West Bank city of Hebron, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
The clash began when Palestinians refused to show their
identity cards to Israeli soldiers guarding the Jewish Quarter,
where there are still some 450 Jewish settlers after Israeli troop
redeployment from 80 percent of the city early this year.
</P>
<P>
Angry Palestinian youths began throwing stones and bottles at
Israeli soldiers who responded with tear gas and rubber
bullets. No injuries and damage were reported in the clash.
</P>
<P>
The latest development in Hebron coincided with a clash in
East Jerusalem's Ras Amud Arab neighborhood, where a group of
Jewish settlers occupied two houses days ago, sparking a new
crisis and tension in the Israeli-Palestinian relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
