<HEADLINE> Kimberly Po Advances to Quarters in Princess Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Fourth seed Kimberly Po of the
United States overcame a 2-5 second-set deficit to beat her
Japanese rival, entering the quarterfinals of the Princess Cup
tennis tournament here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The American downed Rika Hiraki 3-6, 7-6 (8-6), 6-3 by rallying
from 0-3, 1-4, 2-5 in the second set to win the tiebreaker 8-6.
</P>
<P>
Po scored her key break for 5-5, cornering Hiraki into a series
of errors for the tiebreaker where the American gained an initial
6-3 lead before Hiraki levelled 6-6.
</P>
<P>
After squandering her advantage in the second set, Hiraki
surged to a 3-1 lead in the final set but lost all the games
following.
</P>
<P>
Po has reached two semifinals this year, including the Japan
Open in April, and won a tournament in Michigan in February.
</P>
