<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 15th National Party Congress Closes (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) held its closing session after
electing the new CPC Central Committee and the new Central
Commission for Discipline Inspection at the Great Hall of the
People here today.
</P>
<P>
The congress, which opened on the 12th of this month, also
adopted a resolution on the report of the 14th CPC Central
Committee and some other resolutions at today's session.
</P>
<P>
The meeting called on comrades of the entire Party to hold high
the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory and, under the leadership
of the Party central committee, unite and lead the people of
China's all nationalities, to push forward the great cause of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics to the 21st
century with full confidence.
</P>
<P>
Today's session was presided over by Comrade Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Among those seated in the front row on the rostrum were members
of the standing committee of the presidium of the congress,
including Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji,
Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao, Ding Guangen, Tian Jiyun, Li Lanqing, Li
Tieying, Yang Baibing, Wu Bangguo, Zou Jiahua, Jiang Chunyun, Qian
Qichen, Huang Ju, Wei Jianxing, Xie Fei, Wen Jiabao, Wang Hanbin,
Wan Li, Song Ping, Bo Yibo, Zhang Zhen, Zhang Wannian, Chi
Haotian, Ren Jianxin, Ye Xuanping, Wu Xueqian and Hou Zongbin.
</P>
<P>
At 9:00 a.m., Jiang Zemin declared the start of the closing
session.
</P>
<P>
The session first approved a 36-member list of a general
scrutineer and scrutineers.
</P>
<P>
Under the supervision of the general scrutineer and
scrutineers, the 2,074 delegates who were present at the session
cast their secret ballots and elected the 15th CPC Central
Committee composed of 193 members and 151 alternate members. The
delegates also elected the new Central Commission for Discipline
Inspection comprising 115 members.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0191 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 15th National Party Congress Closes (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Great Hall of the People burst into applause when the
results of the election was announced.
</P>
<P>
The session also endorsed a resolution on the report of the
14th CPC Central Committee, approved the report which was
delivered by Jiang Zemin on behalf of the 14th Central Committee,
and highly appraised the work of the 14th Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The congress held that It fully accords with the requirements
of the times and with the aspirations of the people that the
report had affirmed the theme of holding high the great banner of
Deng Xiaoping Theory to push forward, in an all-round way, the
great cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The congress unanimously agreed to establish Deng Xiaoping
Theory as the guiding ideology of the Party and to clearly write
it down into the Party Constitution.
</P>
<P>
The congress agreed on the basic programs of the Party in the
primary stage of socialism set forth in the report, and the
blueprint of China's reform and development in the economic,
political and cultural sectors.
</P>
<P>
The congress approved the plans on national defense and army
building and stressed to realization of the ultimate reunification
of the motherland by adhering to the principle of "one country,
two systems," and agreed on the exposition of the international
situation and various principles on China's foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
The congress stressed that the key to fulfilling the strategic
objectives and various tasks set forth in the report lies in
adhering to, strengthen and improve the leadership of the Party.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
