<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Rice Production May Drop, Official Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's rice production
is likely to drop below the target because of the current drought,
an agriculture ministry official said.
</P>
<P>
"Rice production for 1997 is estimated to reach a little over
50 million tons," the ministry's secretary general Syarifuddin
Karama said on Wednesday, the Antara news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
He said unhulled rice production for this year was estimated to
reach only 50.4 million tons or below 52 million tons which was
the target for the year.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the drought, a total of 21,708 hectares of rice
fields might not be harvested until the end of this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
Drought would likely affect up to 295,785 hectares of rice
fields in the county this year, he added.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, rice supply at the Logistics Bureau (BULOG)
was secure.
</P>
<P>
He said BULOG had been able to collect 1.9 million tons of rice
this year, increasing its supply to 3 million tons which was
enough for six months.
</P>
<P>
The current drought, which began three months ago, is expected
to last till November or December.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
