<HEADLINE> CCDI Work Report Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The work report of the
Central Commission for Discipline Inspection (CCDI) was examined
and approved today at the 15th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
The work of the CCDI was fully affirmed at the congress.
</P>
<P>
The congress asked the CCDI at the central and local levels to
hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, and continue
to do a good job of discipline inspection in accordance with the
responsibilities endowed by the Party Constitution and the
guidelines of the 15th National Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
The congress also required them to have strict political
discipline and guarantee a smooth implementation of the Party's
line and policy decisions set forth by the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The congress called for further efforts to intensify the
fostering of the Party's style of work, and the building of a
clean and honest govenment, and carry out the long-term struggle
against corruption in a profound way for the sake of reforms,
opening-up and stability.
</P>
<P>
Party committees at all levels have been urged to continue to
improve their guidance over the work of discipline inspection at
the congress.
</P>
<P>
They have also been called to adhere to the principle of being
strict with the Party members, further intensify the efforts to
educate the Party members in Party spirit, Party's style of work
and Party discipline so as to maintain the advanced and pure
nature of the Party.
</P>
<P>
The Party committees at all levels have also been urged to
build the Communist Party of China into a Marxist party armed with
Deng Xiaoping Theory, a party which serves the people
whole-heartedly, and is completely consolidated politically,
ideologically and organizationally, and is able to withstand any
risks, and a party which will always march at the forefront of the
times and lead the people across the country to build socialism
with Chinese characteristics. 
</P>
