<HEADLINE> India Police Seize 440 Kilograms of Narcotics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Indian police have recently
seized a record 440 kilograms of hashish valued at 400 million
rupees (about 11.4 million U.S. dollars) in the international
market, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off in the Indian commercial center of Bombay
last week, the police raided a garment factory in the east part of
the city and recovered 440 kilograms of hashish.
</P>
<P>
The contraband was found concealed in cartons, wrapped in
layers of silver foils and adhesive tapes along with motor vehicle
spare parts. It was meant for export to Canada.
</P>
<P>
Five people, who are members of a well-organized syndicate of
international drug-traffickers, were found packing the contraband
and were later arrested.
</P>
<P>
The police have also arrested a few more key members of the
drug syndicate.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
