<HEADLINE> One Die, More Than 40 Injured in U.S. Bus Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- One people was killed and
more than 40 others were injured in a bus crash in western
Arkansas today.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when a tractor-trailer on a winding
mountain road struck a bus, which was carrying 45 people from
North Carolina and South Carolina to Branson, Missouri.
</P>
<P>
The empty trailer sliced through the first three rows of seats
on the bus' left side.
</P>
<P>
Forty-two people were taken to area hospitals. Twenty-seven
were treated and released. The most serious injury was a broken
pelvis. 
