The Treaty of Friendship, Cooperation and Mutual Assistance,
signed by Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Armenian President
Levon Ter-Petrocyan on August 29 in Moscow, aimed to strengthen
the two countries' traditional good relations and all-round
cooperation in political, economic, military, scientific, cultural
and other areas.
</P>
<P>
Primakov said that Russia is also ready to develop relations
with Azerbaijan and that Moscow is willing to sign similar
agreements with it. 
