<HEADLINE> Over 6,700 HIV Carriers Identified in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 18 (xinhua) -- Vietnam detected 6,732 carriers
of HIV, the virus that causes the deadly Acquired
Immuno-Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), in 55 of its 61 provinces and
cities by August, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The National AIDS Committee said 957 of these HIV carriers have
developed full-blown AIDS and 505 of them are dead.
</P>
<P>
Drug injection is a main way of spreading HIV in Vietnam, the
committee was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
A survey indicated AIDS infection through sexual contact is
also on the rise in Vietnam. 
</P>
