<HEADLINE> China Aims to Take 6th Consecutive Asian Volleyball Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese women spikers
will leave here on Friday to compete in the sixth Asian Women's
Volleyball Championship, seeking to take their sixth consecutive
title in Manila.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese, runners-up at the Atlanta Olympic Games, will have
their opener against chief rivals South Korea, which many tipped
as the championship match in advance as all the scores in the
preliminaries will be accounted in the final standings.
</P>
<P>
The sixth championship, inaugurated in 1987 and was held every
two years, will be started on Sunday in the Philippine capital
city of Manila, with the preliminaries to be played in two groups.
</P>
<P>
Group A brackets the Philippines, Australia, Chinese Taipei and
Japan, while China is pitted against Thailand, Uzbekistan, South
Korea and Hong Kong, China in group B.
</P>
<P>
Group winners and runners-up will enter the last four in cross
matches to vie for the top four places.
</P>
<P>
Under the schedule, China will first take South Korea on
Sunday, then against Hong Kong, China on Monday, and Uzbekistan
and Thailand on the following days. 
</P>
