<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0200 GMT, September 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States Wednesday test fired an unarmed
Peacekeeper intercontinental ballistic missile from California to
Marshall Islands.
</P>
<P>
The missile blasted off at 1:01 a.m. local time (0801 GMT) from
Vadenburg Air Force Base, California, and traveled some 4,200
miles (about 7,100 kilometers) in about 30 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Carrying seven unarmed re-entry warheads, it hit a target at
the Kwajalein Missile Range in the western chain of the Marshall
Islands, the Associated Press quoted Air Force officials as
saying. (US-Missile Launch)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SARAJEVO -- A U.N. helicopter with 16 people on board crashed
today in central Bosnia. Twelve people, including a senior
international mediator, were killed, according to AP reports.
</P>
<P>
The only survivors appeared to be the four crew members, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
German envoy Gerd Wagner, one of the most senior diplomats
stationed in Bosnia, was killed in the crash. Wagner, 55, was a
deputy to Carlos Westendorp of Spain, the high representative to
Bosnia in charge of trying to implement peace. (Bosnia-Plane Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
