- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The number of Americans overdue on their
credit-card bills increased sharply during the April-June quarter
after falling a bit in the first quarter, the American Bankers
Association (ABA) said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The delinquency rate -- the percentage of accounts 30 or more
days overdue -- was up to a seasonally adjusted 3.69 percent in
the second quarter from 3.51 percent in the previous three months,
the ABA report said. (U.S.-Credit Card-Delinquency)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOGADISHU -- At least one person was killed and two others were
wounded, one very critical, after rival militiamen exchanged fire
Wednesday afternoon in the center of the busy Bakara market of
South Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said the shooting began when a dispute erupted
between two groups over the building of a new business kiosk in
the market.
</P>
