<HEADLINE> Three Sinhala Films Banned in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Public
Performances Board (PPB) has banned three Sinhala films that
contain explicit sex scenes, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
PPB Chairman Somaratna Balasuriya said the films, titled
"Salupata Ahasata" (Narrow Sky), "Ayadimi Sama" (Distant Peace)
and "Age Vairaya" (Her Revenge), could not be released even as
"very strictly for adults."
</P>
<P>
He said the films were akin to blue movies shown in Western
countries.
</P>
<P>
The board decided to withhold their release after viewing the
films.
</P>
<P>
The PPB had met the producers of the films and requested them
to cut those explicit scenes.
</P>
<P>
But the producers refused to do so and preferred to appeal
against the PPB's decision.  
