<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Cuts Gypsum Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Industry Ministry
has reaffirmed that it would follow the policy to cut gypsum
exports to save the raw material for domestic use.
</P>
<P>
Under the policy, Thailand will reduce gypsum exports by 20
percent each year with an eventual aim to eliminate exports of
gypsum, the ministry said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Thailand has set a quota of 4.24 million tons for gypsum
exports next year with a minimum export price at 17 U.S. dollars
per ton, it added.
</P>
<P>
The Thai government last year introduced a quota policy to
restrict exports of gypsum and save the raw material for domestic
industries to produce higher value-added products for exports.
</P>
<P>
Thailand reportedly is among a few countries in Asia which have
gypsum resources. The country exported 5.3 million tons of gypsum
last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
