<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0250 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former East German Doping Scandal Shocks World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Former East Germany left the
world shocked as systematic doping was disclosed by its biologist
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At a seminar here, German molecular biologist Werner Franke
showed classified documents which detail the exact dosages and
drugs used for the former East German athletes.
</P>
<P>
Some of the athletes named in the documents are still world or
European record holders and some were still in the competitive
arena.
</P>
<P>
Representatives at the seminar expressed shocks at the extent
of the systematic doping, which had affected children as young as
eight and with disturbing side effects particularly on girls.
</P>
<P>
However, to rewrite the record books would be difficult as none
of the East German athletes tested positive during competitions.
</P>
<P>
Currently a two-year ban is imposed in many sports for a
first-time offence, but some said this was not an effective
deterrent because some athletes were willing to take the risk.
</P>
<P>
Franke said the East German records showed that coaches and
team doctors were as much to blame and that many athletes took
drugs unknowingly or under great pressure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
