<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0252 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile Launches Campaign Against Hanta Virus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Chile began to launch a
campaign today to combat Hanta disease which has killed 20 people
in the country.
</P>
<P>
The country has distributed booklets to educate Chilean people
and foreign tourists how to prevent Hanta virus from spreading.
</P>
<P>
Chilean Health Minister Alex Figueroa said today in the
pamphlet that fighting Hanta virus is a task for everyone. The
only way to keep away the infection is taking simple measures,
such as house cleaning and proper disposal of garbage.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Education Minister Jose Pablo Arellano said his
ministry will take part in the campaign, giving instructions to
elementary schools all over the country to educate children not to
contact with rodents, which are the main transmitters of the
sickness.
</P>
<P>
Hanta is a virus transmitted to human body by rodents through
the air, by eating rotten food and contacting rodent excrements
and urine.
</P>
<P>
About 50-60 percent of people infected with the disease will
die, said Marisol Concha, chief of the Epidemiology Department of
the Chilean Health Ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
