<HEADLINE> Nicaragua's Foreign Reserves Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Nicaragua's foreign reserves
dropped to 207.2 million U.S. dollars by September 10, the lowest
level in six years, the Central Bank reported today.
</P>
<P>
Sergio Santamaria, an economist at the Center of Socioeconomic
Research and Consulting, said that the fall may be a result of
government plan to finance the public sector.
</P>
<P>
The government has to use its own resources for this purpose
because it is unable to attract foreign loans for public projects,
Santamaria said. 
</P>
