<HEADLINE> Swedish Borg Avoids Bankruptcy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Former tennis great Bjorn
Borg has avoided bankruptcy after one of his former companies
agreed to pay part of his debt to 11 Swedish creditors.
</P>
<P>
Borg owed them more than 8 million Swedish kronor (about one
million U.S. dollars) and the creditors were said to accept less
than half of that, local reports said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The money will be paid by Worldwide Brand Management owned by
Borg's old friend Anders Arnborger who was also a partner of
Scandinavian Underwear AB which sells underwear, shoes, eyeglasses
and bags under the Bjorn Borg brand.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, Borg paid 40,000 U.S. dollars in taxes
sought by the Swedish tax authorities.
</P>
<P>
Borg's business empire collapsed in 1989.
</P>
<P>
Borg, 41, won an unprecedented five straight Wimbledon titles
from 1976-1980, and also led Sweden to its first Davis Cup title
in 1975. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
