<HEADLINE> Guangxi Promotes Scientific, Technological Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Scientific and technological
undertakings in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region
have experienced a prosperity in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Technological progress projects have helped spur local economic
development, according to an official from the regional government.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, Guangxi's 231 scientific research institutes have
achieved 2,286 findings, and have applied for 6,031 patents,
according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The three foundations in the region have allocated 10 million
yuan for 261 research projects vital to Guangxi's economic and
social develoment.
</P>
<P>
"Four years ago, Guangxi also established three hi-tech
industrial zones in Guilin, Liuzhou, and the regional capital
of Nanning," according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The zones, which are home to 713 enterprises which have carried
out 115 hi-tech production projects, earned 2.1 billion yuan in
industrial output value in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Technological progress has contributed 35 percent to Guangxi's
agricultural growth and 30 percent to its industrial growth over
the past few years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
