<HEADLINE> Jiangxi's Forest Disease Research Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Nankang, a city in east
China's Jiangxi Province, recently opened a scientific research
base, the first of its kind in the country, in terms of prevention
and control of forest disease and for the elimination of pests.
</P>
<P>
The four-staffed research base has had relevant facilities and
a 3.3-hectare forestry nursery with the help of local forestry
department.
</P>
<P>
A four year afforestation effort has expanded Nankang's tree
coverage to over 73,300 ha of masson pines and 13,300 ha of fruit
trees. The city has placed priority on mastering technology to
ensure healthy plant growth, according to local forestry
officials. 
