<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Expands Protection of Cultivated Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region, China's largest autonomous region, is
currently conducting a large-scale investigation of
nonagricultural construction projects on cultivatable land.
</P>
<P>
An official from the region's land administration department
said that nonagricultural construction projects have been
uncovered on 5,000 ha of cultivatable land.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the vast majority of construction projects have
been terminated and that the land has been returned to cultivation.
</P>
<P>
The central government requires all local governments to
terminate construction projects on farmland.
</P>
<P>
The region, which leads all provinces and autonomous regions in
terms of per capita farmland, has introduced tough measures to
control the use of farmland for nonagricultural projects.
</P>
<P>
Local governments are also promoting the protection and
rational use of farmland.
</P>
<P>
The region is currently drafting a comprehensive land-use
plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
