<DOCNO> XIE19970918.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asprilla Scores Hat-Trick for Newcastle in Champions Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Colombian Faustino Asprilla
scored a hat-trick for Newcastle to beat Barcelona 3-2 in one of
12 games that kicked off the Champions Cup soccer tournament on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The talented Colombian converted the first on a penalty in the
22nd minute and headed in the second and third in the 31st and
48th minutes respectively.
</P>
<P>
The penalty kick was argued by Spanish goalie Ruud Hesp as he
dived for a loose ball and Asprilla went down, however his last
two goals were a sure display of skills of a soccer genius.
</P>
<P>
Asprilla's two clean headers were a repeat of feat as he jumped
skyward and knocked in two perfect passes from Keith Gillespie.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona was awakened to a 3-0 deficit and scored its late
goals in the 73rd and 89th minutes through Luis Enrique Martinez
and Luis Figo.
</P>
<P>
Early, Brazilian Rivaldo hit the crossbar in the 79th and the
Spaniards were almost to tie the scoreboard as Christophe Dugarry
sailed a close-in header wide in injury time.
</P>
<P>
In the 24-team competition, Manchester United had a 3-0 win in
Kosice, Slovakia, on goals by Denis Irwin, Henning Berg and Andy
Cole despite the absence of several key players.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, Real Madrid of Spain had a better luck than
Barcelona, beating Norway's Rosenborg 4-1 as Italian Christian
Panucci scored the opener and Alessandro Del Piero added two in
eight minutes.
</P>
<P>
Juventus, runner-up last year, also savored a 5-1 victory over
Feyenoord of the Netherlands through goals from Filippo Inzaghi,
Zinedine Zidane and Alessandro Birindelli.
</P>
<P>
In Istanbul, defending champion Borussia Dortmund beat Turkey's
Galatasaray 1-0 as Stephane Chapuisat intercepted a pass to score
the lone winner in the 74th minute.
</P>
<P>
Bayern Munich won its home game 2-0 over Besiktas of Turkey
through Thomas Helmer and Mario Basler in an otherwise lackluster
match.
</P>
<P>
In other games, Olympiakos Piraeus scored a 1-0 victory over
Portugal's Porto in Athens through Stelios giannacopoulos,
Sporting Lisbon beat Monaco 3-0 at home on goals from Oceano Cruz,
Moroccan striker Mustapha Hadji and Brazilian Leandro Machado.
</P>
<P>
German Bayer Leverkusen won 1-0 over Belgian Lierse SK at home
through a controversial penalty in the 39th minute, Dinamo Kiev
pulled a surprise away win of 3-1 over PSV Eindhoven while Paris
St Germain won 3-0 at home over Goteborg of Sweden and Parma of
Italy played a 0-0 draw at Sparta Prague. 
</P>
</TEXT>
