<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 17 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks were mixed
here today, mostly down from big rallies Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average, which gained 175 points
Tuesday, finished down 9.48 points at 7,886.44.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a slim margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 589.47 million shares,
down from 635.77 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 2.64 to 943.00, the
NYSE composite index fell 0.48 to 493.21, and the Nasdaq composite
index fell 2.13 to 1,666.47.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 rose 0.97 to 446.15. The small-company
dominated American Stock Exchange composite index also closed at a
record high for the fourth straight session, rising 2.95 to 683.00.
</P>
<P>
Bonds rose after a report showing that construction of new
housing unexpectedly slowed 4.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The housing starts data indicated that the economy, though
quite robust, isn't accelerating at an inflationary pace and
reduced the possibility for the Federal Reserve to slow the
economy by raising interest rates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
