<HEADLINE> IDB Approves 180 Mln Dlrs for Urban Upgrading in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 180
million U.S. dollar loan to Brazil to help upgrade urban areas in
Baixada Fluminense region of Rio de Janeiro city.
</P>
<P>
The program includes financing improvements in infrastructure
for such services as basic technical sanitation, street paving,
and recreation. It also provides technical assistance to the
governments of four participating municipalities to help them
better organization and operation of services and establish
financial control systems.
</P>
<P>
Solid waste collection systems, child care centers, primary
health care systems, sanitation and environmental education, and
small business promotion are also among the services that will be
financed.
</P>
<P>
Some 360,000 low-income people are expected to benefit from the
program.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program is estimated at some 300 million
dollars. In addition to the IDB loan, local counterpart funds
total 120 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
