<HEADLINE> Romanian Leaders Meet Finnish FM on EU Entry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Top Romanian leaders have
met Finnish Foreign Minister Tarja Halonen in the past two days
seeking help for the country's entry into the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
In talks with Halonen, who arrived here Tuesday for a two-day
stay, Romanian officials tried to win support from Finland, an EU
member, for their strategies to gain the EU membership.
</P>
<P>
The official lineup included President Emil Constantinescu,
Prime Minister Victor Ciorbea, Chairman of the Senate Petre Roman,
and Halonen's Romanian counterpart, Adrian Severin.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers also discussed opening an air route
between Bucharest and Helsinki, and a land and marine link between
the Baltic Sea and the Black Sea and furthermore the Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
The two-layer link on the land and sea is expected to wind its
way across Finland, the three Baltic countries, Ukraine and
Romania, Severin was quoted as saying by press reports today.
</P>
</TEXT>
