<HEADLINE> Palestinians Protest Against Jewish Settlers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of Palestinians
protesting against Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem clashed
with Israeli riot police this evening.
</P>
<P>
Six demonstrators were arrested.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators, waving Palestinian flags and shouting
slogans of anti-Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem, took to the
street and march toward the two houses in Ras Al-Amud in which
three Jewish families moved in on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
They were stopped by Israeli police on their way.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Peace Now, an Israeli mass organization which is
against the Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem, also
participated in the demonstration.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration is still going on. In order to prevent
further eruption of clashes and confrontation, more Israeli
policemen were called in.
</P>
<P>
Three Jewish families moved into two empty houses in Ras
Al-Amud Arab neighborhood on Sunday night, causing a tense
situation in East Jerusalem. Local Palestinians were angered by
their motive and are determined to kick them out from Ras
Al-Amud.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian National Authority has warned the Israeli
government that allowing the settlers to remain would violate the
peace agreements. The Israeli government has also criticized the
move, but no action has been taken against the settlers. 
</P>
