<HEADLINE> Tibet, Xinjiang Delegates Give Press Conference (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The education in patriotism
which started in May last year focuses mainly on democratic and
legal system, religious policies, safeguarding the unity of the
motherland, and the struggle against splittism, a Tibetan leading
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference today attended by Chinese and
overseas reporters, Raidi, chairman of the Tibet Autonomous
Regional People's Congress, said the education has been carried
out "smoothly and healthily", and has been proved "effective".
</P>
<P>
Raidi is here in Beijing attending the current ongoing
five-yearly Party congress.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the education is to raise the conscientiousness of
the Tibetan monks and nuns to love the motherland and their
religion and abide by laws and regulations, he said, adding
that we aim at building a normal religious order suited to the
socialist society.
</P>
<P>
Raidi refuted the assertion that "the education has infringed
upon religious freedom", pointing out that "no country virtually
allows social organizations or people to violate laws, or allows
law-breaking activities under the pretext of religion."
</P>
<P>
"For over a decade, construction of temples and the recruiting
of Buddhist monks and nons were not standardized. Moreover the
Dalai Lama has been carrying out separative activities," Raidi
said, adding that "these factors gave rise to some activities that
breached either the law or the Buddhist doctrines."
</P>
<P>
In responding to a question on the current situation in
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Wang Lequan, secretary of the
Regional Party Committee, said the political and social situation
in the region is stable.
</P>
<P>
"Not long ago," Wang said, "a small number of people stirred up
a riot, which was very unpopular and was firmly opposed by
people of various nationalities in the region."
</P>
<P>
Speaking of Dalai Lama's recent so-called advocation for
non-violence, Raidi pinpointed that Dalai has been carrying out
separative activities all the time since he fled to foreign
countries.
</P>
<P>
"Splittists headed by Dalai have stirred up many riots in
collusion with Western hostile forces, which has disturbed the
peaceful life of the Tibetan," Raidi said, asking how can you say
what he has done was for peace.
</P>
</TEXT>
