<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Subcommittee Discusses Impact of Sports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The European Union
subcommittee of the regions today devoted a full session to sports
as it discussed the impact that sports have on cities and regions,
both economically and culturally.
</P>
<P>
At its September plenary session, the committee delved into the
function of sports as a vehicle for demonstrating the identity of
regions and cities that have hosted or plan to host Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The 222 committee members were joined by Juan Antonio
Samaranch, president of the International Olympic Committee (IOC),
and a dozen of other sporting event organizers, club managers and
sporting stars as guest speakers.
</P>
<P>
The session was presided over by committee president and
Barcelona mayor Pasqual Maragall. His Spanish city played host to
the 1992 Summer Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
"For the individual, sport is a source of health, passion and
quality of life," he told the session held in the form of
round-table discussion. "Sport is increasingly a part of our
culture and plays an important educational role.
</P>
<P>
"For communities of citizens, sport is also a vehicle of
cultural identity and a facet of socio-economic development.
Sometimes, sport can become a center for passions or political
interests."
</P>
<P>
It was for such a rationale that the EU Amsterdam Treaty, a
revision of the Maastricht Treaty has included sport as one of the
factors for drawing the peoples of the 15-nation union closer
together.
</P>
<P>
When asked what an ideal organization of the Olympic Games is,
the IOC chief, who was reelected on September 5 for another
four-year term, said that an ideal organization is to have
contributions from the private sectors of a society.
</P>
<P>
"It is ideal for an Olympics to be half-funded by private
sectors and half-funded by public sectors," Samaranch said.
</P>
<P>
After announcing that Barcelona and Athens of Greece have just
forged a sister-city relationship, the Barcelona mayor said that
his advice to his Athens counterpart, Dimitris Avramopoulos, was
that each Olympic host city has to have its own project so as to
make its games different.
</P>
<P>
The Greek city has just won the rights to host the 2004 summer
Olympic Games, beating rivals of Rome of Italy, Cape Town of South
Africa, Stockholm of Sweden and Buenos Aires of Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Both committee members and guest speakers also touched upon
such topics as sports in view of regional economic development
such as employment and construction of infrastructure and sports
in view of social cohesion within a society.
</P>
<P>
After the plenary session, Maragall, Samaranch and committee
members visited an exhibition showcasing the interrelations
between sports and regional and municipal economies and cultures.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
