<HEADLINE> Fighting Erupted in Somali Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, September 17 (Xinhua) -- At least one person was
killed and two others were wounded, one very critical, after
rival militiamen exchanged fire this afternoon in the center of
the busy Bakara market of South Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said the shooting began when a dispute erupted
between two groups over the building of a new business kiosk in
the market.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the market said the dispute came after a group of
businessmen who owned a commercial store were attacked by about
six gunmen who wanted to build the kiosk right in front of their
store.
</P>
<P>
The store keepers defended themselves and returned fire. Store
owners nearby also opened fire in an attempt to stop the looters
taking chances from the trouble in the market.
</P>
<P>
The disputed area itself is not owned by any of the two groups
since it was one of the runways left for public use by the late
government for the smooth movements within the market. Many of
the runways and roads leading to and from Bakara market have
already been built by greedy business people taking advantage of
the anarchy and lawlessness in the country.
</P>
<P>
Other unconfirmed reports said the gunmen who attacked the
area have been looking for the other group for retaliatory
purpose.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the shooting has resulted in the immediate
closure of all business stalls surrounding the area where the
incident took place. Other businessmen have called up their
gunmen to strengthen the security of the area which was
immediately deserted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
