<HEADLINE> UNOSOM Accused of Committing Human Rights Abuses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Lawyers here claimed that
more cases of human rights abuses committed by the contingents
from the multi-national forces of UNOSOM during their stay in
Somalia are bringing up here in the capital Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Ilyas Hagi Mohamud, one of the lawyers of the Somali
Intellectual Society (SIS), said they have 97 more cases of human
rights abuses committed by Italian soldiers in the U.N. Operation
in Somalia (UNOSOM), which vary from killing, torture and rape.
</P>
<P>
All the victims in the years of 1992 and 1993 and early 1994
need to be compensated, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued by the SIS, the lawyers said the Italian
committee investigating their soldiers' human rights abuses
should realize the extent of inhuman activities done by the
soldiers in Mogadishu and its surrounding districts and villages.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, SIS said there are also some cases involving the
Belgian forces in Kismayu, 500 km south of the capital.
</P>
<P>
In Kismayu itself, a local human rights organization, the
Jubbaland Human Rights, has revealed that the Belgian forces have
been charged for 137 cases, of which 84 are killings.
</P>
<P>
The Jubbaland Human Rights has condemned the judicial system
of the Belgian government, saying that Belgium has only surfaced
one case out of the large numbers in which the soldier was
acquitted. 
</P>
