<HEADLINE> IDB Okays First Financing to Uruguay from Private </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of the first
financing to Uruguay from the Private Sector Department.
</P>
<P>
The first financing of some 25 million U.S. dollars is provided
for the construction, operation and maintenance of a 132-km
highway linking Montevideo with Punta del Este, as well as other
access roads.
</P>
<P>
The financing consists of two loans, a direct loan of 12
million dollars to the project company, Consorcio del Este, and a
syndicated loan of 13 million dollars with funds provided by
commercial banks under participation agreements with IDB.
</P>
<P>
The project will lead to greater private sector participation
in the Uruguayan economy and expansion and improvement of
transportation from the capital to Punta de Este, a tourism center
that produces a major share of the country's foreign exchange
earnings.
</P>
<P>
After completion of the project, 90 percent of the highway
between Montevideo and Punta del Este will be a two-lane toll road
in either direction.
</P>
<P>
The project is the first IDB financing for Uruguay from the
Private Sector Department, which lends directly to the private
sector without government guarantees. It is also the first highway
concession granted by the Uruguay government to the private sector
to operate a facility that was formerly in the public domain.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
