<HEADLINE> Annan Expresses Shock Over UN Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan was shocked and deeply saddeded by the news this
morning about the crash of a United Nations helicopter in Bosnia
and Herzegovina, said a statement by the spokesman's office.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter was carrying 12 members of the United Nations
International Police Task Force and of the office of the High
Representative, as well as four crew members. According to the
initial reports, 11 persons were killed and five survived the
crash.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the secretary-general was following the
developments closely and he expressed his heartfelt condolences to
the families of those who were killed in the crash. He hoped for a
speed recovery of the survivors.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief wished to thank the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization-led Stabilization Force in Bosnia and Herzegovina
which conducted the search and rescue operation and in whose
medical facilities the survivors are being cared for. 
</P>
