<HEADLINE> Four Women Candidates to Vie for Irish Presidency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Ireland's presidential
election, to be held on October 30, is to be fought by four women
contestants with the ruling Fianna Fail Party picking law
professor Mary McAleese as its candidate early today.
</P>
<P>
The Fianna Fail, which won a cliff-hanger election victory in
June, abandoned former Prime Minister Albert Reynolds, who played
a major role in the Northern Ireland peace process.
</P>
