<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Altogether 13 candidates for
the upcoming Camerounian presidential election have submitted
their files to the Ministry of Territorial Administration as the
deadline expires today for the deposit of candidate file.
</P>
<P>
The 13 presidential candidates include such prominent figures
as Paul Biya, president and national chairman of the ruling
Cameroun People's Democratic Movement (CDPM), and Samuel Eboua,
chairman of the Democratic and Progress Movement (MDP).
</P>
<P>
Victorin Hameni Bieleu, president of the Cameroun Democratic
Force Union (UFDC), and Hogbe Nleud, candidate for the Cameroun
People's Union (UPC), are also among them.
</P>
<P>
The list of candidates shows that Marcus Onana Mouma is the
only independent candidate that belongs to no party.
</P>
<P>
The country's three major opposition parties, the Social
Democratic Front (SDF) and the National Union for Democracy and
Progress (NUDP) and the Camerounian Democratic Union (CDU) have
decided earlier this week to boycott the presidential election
scheduled for October 12.
</P>
<P>
According to Cameroun's electoral law, the electoral campaign
will start on September 27 all over the country. 
</P>
